Scope; Partner Sites
This Privacy Policy applies to Personal Information we collect through our Site, App, home security devices and other interactions with you including email and phone. Our Site contains links to partner sites that are not owned or controlled by SimpliSafe. Please be aware that we are not responsible for the privacy practices of these other sites. We encourage you to be aware when you leave our Site and to read the privacy statements of these other sites that collect your Personal Information.
Additional Terms
Please reference our
Terms of Sale
which apply to your purchase of our products. Please also note that use of our Site and App are subject to the
Website Terms of Use
. Moreover, if you subscribe to SimpliSafe’s monitoring services, features connected with those services or activate service offerings made available in connection with a SimpliSafe product that do not require a monitoring subscription, use of those features and services are also subject to the
Terms of Service
.
2. INFORMATION WE COLLECT AND WHY WE COLLECT IT
SimpliSafe collects Personal Information to enable you to take full advantage of our offerings when you register on our Site, order products or services either through the Site or through our call center, use our App, communicate with customer service representatives (including via the online chat function), participate in our contests, surveys, promotions, or activities or otherwise communicate with us. If you choose, you can visit the Site without directly providing us with any Personal Information.
We seek to limit the collection and use of customer Personal Information required to deliver service to our customers. The purposes for which we collect customer Personal Information include advising our customers about our products, services and other opportunities, advertising our products and services, and administering our business.
Individuals That Visit Our Site or Interact With Us:
We may collect the following categories of Personal Information:
Identifiers
(such as your name, address, email address, telephone number, unique device identifiers for mobile devices or tablets, visitor identification number, and IP address)
Commercial information
(such as products or services you considered, or other purchasing or consuming information)
Internet or other electronic network activity
(such as information about your interaction with our Site, your browser type, computer or device type, visitor identification number, operating system version, the website you navigated from to reach out site, timestamp information about your visit to our Site, the pages on our Site that you view, including pages visited, session replay of your journey through our Site, and the name of your internet service provider)
Inferences
(such as creating a profile about your preferences based on your interaction with us and our website)
Geolocation data
(such as your approximate location based on IP address)
Our sources for this Personal Information:
We receive this Personal Information directly from you when you provide it to us, participate in our contests, surveys, promotions or other activities, and when you communicate with us, including any Personal Information you provide to customer service either during a phone call, by email or text, or online live chat
Some of this Personal Information is collected automatically when you visit the Site or use our App
We receive some of this Personal Information from our advertising partners
Our business purposes for collecting this Personal Information:
To send you updates about new products and to suggest products and services to you that we think you may be interested in
To operate and improve our business, products and services, the Site and the App, including Quality Assurance (QA) for certain types of interactions we have with you such as through Site chat and Customer Service calls
To service your requests, to contact you when necessary or requested, including responding to your questions and comments and providing customer support, to obtain customer feedback and improve our customer service and customer shopping experience, and to enable the communication through technical service providers
For a limited number of Website visitors, to create a session replay that shows your visit to our site in order to identify and troubleshoot functionality issues
Service Providers we disclose this information to:
Certain Service Providers that help us to host our website, send email updates about the website and remove repetitive information from our user lists
Analytics partners such as Facebook, Amplitude and Google
Service Providers that allow us to maintain the integrity and security of your Site and App experience
Service Providers who assist us with customer service and product development
Any other person or entity we reasonably think is customary, necessary or advisable for the business purposes disclosed in this Privacy Policy or to whom we are obliged by applicable law or regulation to make the disclosure
Third parties we “share” (as defined in the California Consumer Privacy Act) this Personal Information with:
We may share your Personal Information, including Personal Information about how you browse and shop, with certain strategic partners and other third parties that provide offers we think may be of value to you
We belong to ad networks that may use your browsing history across participating websites to show you internet-based advertisements on those websites
We work with advertising partners such as Facebook and Google to deliver advertisements tailored to your interests
For the avoidance of doubt, we do not sell or share your Personal Information for marketing purposes when that Personal Information was obtained through short code messaging.
SimpliSafe Customers:
In addition to the Personal Information above, if you have purchased a SimpliSafe product or service, we may have collected the following categories of Personal Information:
Identifiers
(such as your email, phone number, address, device usage information and information about your household. We additionally may collect contact information of users’ family and friends for alarm notification purposes or for our “Tell-A-Friend” program)
Commercial information
(such as your purchase history and information about your product usage)
Financial Information
(SimpliSafe partners with Chase Bank for processing credit or debit payments that you initiate onsite and we will only store the last 4 digits of your payment card and expiration date)
Internet or other electronic network activity
(such as information about your and your devices’ interaction with our network, your interaction with our Site and App, your visitor identification number, your product usage, the website you navigated from to reach our site, timestamp information about your visit to our site, the pages on our site that you view, including pages visited, your mouse movement and keystrokes for evaluating site functionality, and the name of your internet service provider)
Audio, visual and similar information
(if you use our security cameras or other camera-enabled products, we collect information such as audio and video recordings from such devices so that we can provide the guaranteed services)
Inferences
(such as a profile based on information reflecting your activity and preferences)
Geolocation Information (as necessary to utilize Bluetooth and Wifi functionality of our products and services.
Precise geolocation is only collected in a one-time fashion in order to enable Wifi capabilities, other instances of Geolocation collection are coarse
)
Sensitive Personal Information
(combination of email address and password, or other credentials, such as safeword, allowing access to your account; and protected classification characteristics, if you voluntarily provide them in response to our surveys, such as your race and ethnicity)
Our sources for this Personal Information:
Communications we have with you in any way including in person, by phone, online, by email or text, or by online live chat. Please note that we record and save calls involving our customer service team and any online chats
Your interaction with the Site and the App, both in the form of Personal Information collected automatically and provided directly by you
If you add a Live Guard Protect capable camera and enable this feature,we may collect video recordings and associated audio when a recording is initiated or when you interact with our monitoring agents as part of the Live Guard Protection feature. Find more on Live Guard Protection by visiting our Help Center
We receive this Personal Information directly from you when you purchase, setup and use our products and services, and when you communicate with us
We sometimes combine information that you voluntarily provide to us with information that we automatically collect when you visit our websites or interact with our products and services
We receive this Personal Information from analytics partners and advertising and marketing companies
Our business purposes for collecting this Personal Information:
To deliver our products and services to you, such as our Video Verification and Live Guard Protection features
To send you alarm alerts and important service information about your alarm and our services
To communicate with you about your orders and purchases
To send you updates about new products and to suggest products and services to you that we think you may be interested in
To provide monitoring services to you, if you enable them
To detect, prevent or otherwise address fraud, security or technical issues
To operate and improve our business, products and services, Site, and Apps
To advertise and market our products and services
To gather feedback on our products and services as well as your interactions with the company
To evaluate analytics Personal Information to improve the performance of our Site, products, services and Apps
To analyze customer interactions for QA purposes where you have consented to such processing
To provide customer service
Service Providers we disclose this Personal Information to:
Service Providers that help us process orders and fulfill and deliver products and services that you purchase from us. If you choose to enable account connections or integrations with third-party products such as SimpliSafe’s Amazon Alexa Skill, Apple Watch or Google Assistant, we may share your Personal Information. This is only done with your consent, and you can revoke or disable these connections and integrations at any time
If you subscribe to our monitoring or emergency dispatch services, we disclose your Personal Information to Service Providers to facilitate those services
We use Service Providers to host our Site, send out email updates about the Site, provide marketing and advertising services for us, remove repetitive Personal Information from our user lists, and process payments
Service Providers that conduct research surveys, focus groups and promote contests
Our Service Providers, such as our website and cloud hosting providers
Partners such as AARP and Farmer’s Insurance when you have utilized discounts and promotions that those groups make available
If you request system setup assistance, we disclose your information to Service Providers to assist you with setup services
Third parties we “share” (as defined in the California Consumer Privacy Act) this Personal Information with:
We may share your Personal Information, including Personal Information about how you browse and shop, with certain strategic partners and other third-parties that provide offers we think may be of value to you
We belong to ad networks that may use your browsing history across participating websites to show you internet-based advertisements on those websites
We work with advertising partners such as Facebook and Google to deliver advertisements tailored to your interests
For the avoidance of doubt, we do not sell or share your Personal Information for marketing purposes when that Personal Information was obtained through short code messaging.
Sensitive Personal Information
Your sensitive Personal Information will not be used for any additional purposes that are incompatible with the purposes listed above, unless we provide you with notice of those additional purposes or gather your consent as required by law.
Personal Information Collected through the Security Camera or other Camera-Enabled Products
When you enable the recording features of your security camera or other camera-enabled products (for example, SimpliSafe’s video doorbell product), we will record, store and process video and/or audio recordings from the device, depending on how you configure the camera and its settings. This may include capturing and making available to you portions of the recording data as part of a notification or analysis of the data to identify motion or other events. We process and store Personal Information from your camera-enabled product so that we can send you alerts when there is an event. If you have the recording features enabled, during the subscription period applicable to your camera-enabled product we will capture, process and store video and audio recordings from your camera for 30 days from the date such data is first recorded ("SimpliSafe's date of first capture"). During your subscription period, you will be able to access those recordings for 30 days from SimpliSafe's date of first capture of such data. You have the option to delete and download these recordings from your account timeline during that 30-day window. If you choose to download a recording, it will not impact the retention of these videos on SimpliSafe’s systems.
NOTE: Privacy laws in your state may impose certain obligations on you and your use of the security camera(s) or other camera-enabled products. You (not SimpliSafe) are solely responsible for ensuring that you comply with any applicable laws when you use such camera-enabled products. For example, you may be required to display a notice (even inside your home) that alerts visitors to your home that you are using a security camera or other camera-enabled products that are recording audio and video. Please also consider that recording and sharing of video that involves other people may affect their privacy rights.
Cookies, Pixels, Advertising Partners and Analytics Partners
We use analytics Service Providers to collect certain Personal Information about how our Site is used. We and our advertising and analytics partners use cookies and pixels (also called web beacons) to collect certain types of Personal Information when you interact with our Site through your computer or mobile device.
A cookie is a small file containing a string of characters that is sent to your web browser when you visit a website. When you visit the website again from that web browser, the cookie allows that site to recognize your browser and, potentially, device. Cookies may store unique identifiers, user preferences and other Personal Information. You can direct your browser to clear all cookies or use the browser to understand which cookies are being set and what network requests are being made by our site. However, some website features or services may not function properly without cookies. We use cookies to improve the quality of our service, including storing user preferences, tracking user trends and providing relevant advertising to you.
Currently, we use analytics partners such as Google Analytics, Facebook, Optimizely, Amplitude and FullStory. In order to make sure you understand how our analytics partners handle your Personal Information and how they interact with our Site, you should visit the pages linked below for more information.
Google Analytics uses cookies and pixels to help us understand how visitors use our Site and to collect data on website activity. For more information regarding Google Analytics please visit
http://www.google.com/analytics/terms/us.html
. For information on how to opt out of Google Analytics, please visit
https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout/
.
Optimizely is a third-party website optimization service that analyzes your use of our Site and our relationship with you, so that we can improve our Site. For more information on the privacy practices of Optimizely, please visit
https://www.optimizely.com/privacy
. You can opt out from Optimizely at any time by following the instructions at
http://www.optimizely.com/opt_out
.
FullStory is a session recording technology that we use on our Site to detect anomalous site behavior and fix site functionality issues. For more information on the privacy practices of FullStory, please check
https://www.fullstory.com/legal/privacy-policy
.
We belong to ad networks that may use your browsing history across participating websites to show you interest-based advertisements on those websites. To learn more about interest-based advertisements and your opt-out rights and options, visit the
Digital Advertising Alliance
and the
Network Advertising Initiative
websites.
If your internet browser offers “Do Not Track” or the “Global Privacy Control” opt-out preference signal and you enable the feature, we will honor your request to opt-out of sale or sharing when you visit our Site by treating the requests as an opt-out of cookies and pixels that collect and share information for marketing purposes.
SimpliSafe Product or Account Interaction with SimpliSafe Partners
If SimpliSafe offers any product or account connections or integrations with partner products, applications, functionality or services (collectively, “Partner Products and Services”) and if you choose to enable or connect to such Partner Products and Services through the means authorized and directed by SimpliSafe and/or such partners, then you acknowledge and agree that we may share certain Personal Information about you with such partners for account authentication and management and to enable the activation, and integration with and connection to such Partner Products and Services on such partners’ platforms. For example, when you elect to use Partner Products and Services, such as SimpliSafe’s Amazon Alexa Skill, the August Smart Lock, Apple Watch or Google Assistant (as and when each is introduced), you agree that we may provide certain data about you to such partners in order to enable the activation, connection and integration with and to such Partner Products and Services you intend to use or otherwise choose to activate. In some cases, SimpliSafe or the partner will instead (or also) ask for permission to control the SimpliSafe products and services and/or Partner Products and Services that you have activated and connected to as contemplated hereunder. Your consent is required to allow any of these exchanges or requests for control and you will be able to revoke or disable it at any time.
In addition, SimpliSafe may share Personal Information with such partners with your permission. For example, when you enroll or activate Partner Products and Services, you may be asked for your permission to share certain data between SimpliSafe and our partner. SimpliSafe requires your consent before sharing Personal Information in these circumstances. We may also receive information from our partners and other sources and combine that with the Personal Information in your SimpliSafe account to determine eligibility and efficacy of our programs.
Additional information about the limited circumstances in which Personal Information from your SimpliSafe account may be shared with partners is described in the section titled "
Information We Collect and Why We Collect It
."
Any SimpliSafe data that you choose to share with a partner, either directly or by or on behalf of SimpliSafe through the authorizations, integrations and connections permitted under this Privacy Policy, is governed by that partner’s privacy policy.
Any data that SimpliSafe receives from partners will be processed and stored by SimpliSafe and will be treated in accordance with this Privacy Policy. This information may be processed in the same ways as any other data that is a part of your SimpliSafe account.
No Personal Information From Children or Teens Under Age 18
This Site is not directed to, and we do not knowingly collect any Personal Information from, children or teenagers under the age of 18. If you are under the age of 18, please do not attempt to register with us at this Site or provide any Personal Information about yourself to us. If you are under the age of 18, you may only use this Site under the supervision of your parents or guardians.
The Site does not knowingly solicit or collect personally identifiable information online from children under the age of 13 without prior verifiable parental consent. If we learn that a child under the age of 13 has submitted personally identifiable information online without parental consent, SimpliSafe will take all reasonable measures to delete such information from its databases, inform any third parties to delete such information and to not use such information for any purpose (except where necessary to protect the safety of the child or others as required or allowed by law). If you become aware of any personally identifiable information we have collected from children under 13, please use the
contact form available on our website
.
We do not have actual knowledge that we sell or share Personal Information of individuals under 16 years of age.
Third-Party Sites and Social Media
Our Site may contain links to other websites operated by third parties and may include social media features such as Facebook, Twitter and Pinterest buttons. These third-party sites may collect Personal Information about you if you click on a link, and the social media sites may automatically record Personal Information about your browsing behavior every time you visit a site that has a social media button. Your interactions with these features are governed by the privacy policy and terms of service of the company providing the link, not SimpliSafe’s Privacy Policy or Terms of Service. Accordingly, we recommend that you review the privacy policy posted on any external site before disclosing any Personal Information. Please contact those websites directly if you have any questions about their privacy policies.
Refer A Friend
If you use our “Refer A Friend” feature, we ask for your friend’s name and e-mail address. We use this Personal Information only to send the communication you requested and to monitor the effectiveness of our “Refer A Friend” feature.
Legal Proceedings
We will share Personal Information with third-party companies, organizations or individuals outside of SimpliSafe if we have a good-faith belief that access, use, preservation or disclosure of the Personal Information is reasonably necessary to:
Meet any applicable law, regulation, subpoena, legal process or governmental request.
Enforce applicable
Terms of Sale
,
Terms of Use
, and
Terms of Service
, including investigation of potential violations.
Detect, prevent or otherwise address fraud, security or technical issues.
Protect against harm to the rights, property or safety of SimpliSafe, our users, customers or the public as required or permitted by law.
Under certain circumstances, we may be required to disclose your Personal Information in response to valid requests by public authorities, including to meet national security or law enforcement requirements.
Transfer in the Event of Sale or Change of Control
If the ownership of all or substantially all of our business changes or we otherwise transfer assets relating to our business or the Site to a third party, such as by merger, acquisition, bankruptcy proceeding or otherwise, we may transfer or sell your Personal Information to the new owner. In such a case, unless permitted or otherwise directed by applicable law, your Personal Information would remain subject to the terms of the applicable privacy policy in effect at the time of such transfer.
3. ACCESS TO YOUR INFORMATION AND CHOICES
You can access and update certain Personal Information we have relating to your account by logging into your account via our online web application at
simplisafe.com
or in our mobile App. To update your contact information for your alarm monitoring and dispatch, navigate to the “Monitoring” section. To update your login information (email, password), you can navigate to the “Manage Account” section.
To update your contact information for your alarm monitoring and dispatch on our mobile App, you can log in and tap on the menu and select “Location Profile”. To update your login information on our mobile App (email, password), you can tap on the menu and select “Manage Account”.
If you have questions about the Personal Information we have about you, you can
Contact Us using this form
. You may opt out of receiving non-marketing related communications (this does not include alarm alerts and service information) from us by logging into your account and editing your notification preferences. You can opt-out of receiving marketing and promotional emails from SimpliSafe by using the opt-out or unsubscribe feature contained in the footer of our marketing emails.
You can close your online account by calling us at 800-548-9508. If you close your account, we will no longer use your online account information or share it with third parties. We may, however, retain some of your Personal Information, as allowed by law, for a period of time reasonably necessary for legitimate business purposes, archival purposes and to avoid identity theft or fraud.
4. SECURITY OF YOUR INFORMATION
We use commercially reasonable physical, technical and administrative security measures and safeguards to protect the confidentiality and security of your Personal Information. However, since the Internet is not a 100% secure environment, we cannot guarantee, ensure or warrant the security of any Personal Information you transmit to us. There is no guarantee that Personal Information may not be accessed, disclosed, altered or destroyed by breach of any of our physical, technical or managerial safeguards. Please note that e-mails and other communications you send to us through our Site are not encrypted, outside of certain channels such as secure chat, and we strongly advise you not to communicate any confidential information through these means.
5. CALIFORNIA AND OTHER STATE PRIVACY RIGHTS
If you are a resident of California, Virginia, Colorado, Connecticut,  Utah, Texas, Oregon, Montana (starting October 1, 2024), Nebraska (starting January 1, 2025), Iowa (starting January 1, 2025), Delaware (starting January 1, 2025), New Hampshire (starting January 1, 2025), or New Jersey (starting January 15, 2025) the privacy laws in those states provide you with several rights with respect to your personal information. Please see your state specific sections below for more information.
Your California Privacy Rights
The Right to Know dictates, upon your request, that we will provide you with any of the following:
what Personal Information we have collected, used, disclosed and “sold” about you, including the categories of Personal Information
the categories of sources from which the Personal Information is collected
the business or commercial purpose(s) for collecting, selling, or sharing Personal Information
the categories of third parties to whom SimpliSafe discloses Personal Information
the specific pieces of Personal Information SimpliSafe has collected about you.
The Right to Correct inaccuracies in your Personal Information, taking into account the nature of the Personal Information and the purposes of the processing. For more information about how to exercise this right, please see
this section of our Privacy Policy
.
The right to request that we delete any Personal Information we have collected about you. Please note this right is not absolute and that SimpliSafe will, in some cases, retain Personal Information as allowed by applicable laws and to support essential functionality, such as maintaining your subscription.
The right to opt-out of the selling or sharing of your Personal Information, which you can exercise through this form
Do Not Sell My Personal Information
. Please note that clearing your cookies at any time will remove your selected opt-out preferences.
The right to limit the use of your sensitive Personal Information, which you can exercise through this form
Do Not Sell My Personal Information
.
To exercise the above rights, you may use this form to opt out of the sale and sharing of Personal Information
Do Not Sell My Personal Information
or
this form
to exercise your right to know, right to deletion and/or right to correction. You may also designate an authorized agent to make a request on your behalf on our website through
this form
.
When you exercise these rights and submit a request to us, we will verify your identity by asking you to confirm some of your Personal Information that SimpliSafe currently holds such as your email address, order numbers of previous orders of our products and services, your equipment serial numbers or the last four digits of a credit or debit card used to make a purchase. We will endeavor to honor such requests unless such a request conflicts with certain lawful exemptions granted by the California Consumer Privacy Act. Please note that we are only required to honor Right to Know requests twice in a 12-month period.
We do not discriminate against California residents who exercise any of their rights described in our Privacy Policy. Your exercise of these rights will have no adverse effect on the price and quality of our goods or services.
In addition, and as set forth below, California law requires us to identify, for the 12-month period prior to the date of this Privacy Policy, what Personal Information we may have “sold” or “shared” about you. For the 12-month period prior to the date of this Privacy Policy, SimpliSafe has only sold or shared Personal Information about its customers as described in this Privacy Policy. SimpliSafe does not use or disclose sensitive Personal Information, as defined in applicable laws, for any purposes other than those permitted by applicable law.
If your internet browser offers “Do Not Track” or the “Global Privacy Control” opt-out preference signal, and you enable the feature, we will honor your request to opt-out of sale or sharing when you visit our Site by treating these as an opt-out of cookies and pixels that collect and share information for marketing purposes. As mentioned above, you may also opt-out of the use of third-party cookies for personalized advertising by setting your cookie preferences on your browser or by navigating to our opt-out of sale preference center here:
Do Not Sell My Personal Information
This Privacy Policy describes how we may share your Personal Information for marketing purposes, as described above. If you are a California resident, the Shine the Light law permits you to request and obtain from us once per calendar year information about any of your Personal Information shared with third parties for their own direct marketing purposes, including the categories of information and the names and addresses of those businesses with which we have shared such information. To request this information and for any other questions about our privacy practices and compliance with California law, please contact us through our website:
Contact us
.
Your Virginia, Colorado, Connecticut, Oregon, Texas, Montana (starting October 1, 2024), Nebraska (starting January 1, 2025), Delaware (starting January 1, 2025), New Hampshire (starting January 1, 2025), and New Jersey (starting January 15, 2025
)
Privacy Rights
