The right to correct inaccuracies in your Personal Information, taking into account the nature of the Personal Information and the purposes of the processing. For more information about how to perform this action, please see
this section of our Privacy Policy
.
The right to delete Personal Information we have about you. Please note this right is not absolute and that SimpliSafe will, in some cases, retain Personal Information as allowed by applicable laws and to support essential functionality, such as maintaining your subscription.
The right to opt out of the processing of your Personal Information for purposes of targeted advertising, the sale of Personal Information, and/or profiling in furtherance of decisions that produce legal or similarly significant effects.
The right to obtain a copy of Personal Information we have obtained about you in a portable and, to the extent technically feasible, readily usable format.
Please note that SimpliSafe
does not
process your Personal Information using machine learning and/or profiling methods in ways that would impact you in a legal or similarly significant manner, without your consent.
If we deny your request, the right to appeal our decision.
