. Moreover, if you subscribe to SimpliSafe’s monitoring services, features connected with those services or activate service offerings made available in connection with a SimpliSafe product that do not require a monitoring subscription, use of those features and services are also subject to the
Terms of Service
.
2. INFORMATION WE COLLECT AND WHY WE COLLECT IT
SimpliSafe collects Personal Information to enable you to take full advantage of our offerings when you register on our Site, order products or services either through the Site or through our call center, use our App, communicate with customer service representatives (including via the online chat function), participate in our contests, surveys, promotions, or activities or otherwise communicate with us. If you choose, you can visit the Site without directly providing us with any Personal Information.
We seek to limit the collection and use of customer Personal Information required to deliver service to our customers. The purposes for which we collect customer Personal Information include advising our customers about our products, services and other opportunities, advertising our products and services, and administering our business.
Individuals That Visit Our Site or Interact With Us:
We may collect the following categories of Personal Information:
Identifiers
(such as your name, address, email address, telephone number, unique device identifiers for mobile devices or tablets, visitor identification number, and IP address)
Commercial information
(such as products or services you considered, or other purchasing or consuming information)
Internet or other electronic network activity
(such as information about your interaction with our Site, your browser type, computer or device type, visitor identification number, operating system version, the website you navigated from to reach out site, timestamp information about your visit to our Site, the pages on our Site that you view, including pages visited, session replay of your journey through our Site, and the name of your internet service provider)
Inferences
(such as creating a profile about your preferences based on your interaction with us and our website)
Geolocation data
(such as your approximate location based on IP address)
Our sources for this Personal Information:
We receive this Personal Information directly from you when you provide it to us, participate in our contests, surveys, promotions or other activities, and when you communicate with us, including any Personal Information you provide to customer service either during a phone call, by email or text, or online live chat
Some of this Personal Information is collected automatically when you visit the Site or use our App
We receive some of this Personal Information from our advertising partners
Our business purposes for collecting this Personal Information:
To send you updates about new products and to suggest products and services to you that we think you may be interested in
To operate and improve our business, products and services, the Site and the App, including Quality Assurance (QA) for certain types of interactions we have with you such as through Site chat and Customer Service calls
To service your requests, to contact you when necessary or requested, including responding to your questions and comments and providing customer support, to obtain customer feedback and improve our customer service and customer shopping experience, and to enable the communication through technical service providers
For a limited number of Website visitors, to create a session replay that shows your visit to our site in order to identify and troubleshoot functionality issues
Service Providers we disclose this information to:
Certain Service Providers that help us to host our website, send email updates about the website and remove repetitive information from our user lists
Analytics partners such as Facebook, Amplitude and Google
Service Providers that allow us to maintain the integrity and security of your Site and App experience
Service Providers who assist us with customer service and product development
Any other person or entity we reasonably think is customary, necessary or advisable for the business purposes disclosed in this Privacy Policy or to whom we are obliged by applicable law or regulation to make the disclosure
Third parties we “share” (as defined in the California Consumer Privacy Act) this Personal Information with:
We may share your Personal Information, including Personal Information about how you browse and shop, with certain strategic partners and other third parties that provide offers we think may be of value to you
We belong to ad networks that may use your browsing history across participating websites to show you internet-based advertisements on those websites
We work with advertising partners such as Facebook and Google to deliver advertisements tailored to your interests
For the avoidance of doubt, we do not sell or share your Personal Information for marketing purposes when that Personal Information was obtained through short code messaging.
