Sensitive Personal Information
Your sensitive Personal Information will not be used for any additional purposes that are incompatible with the purposes listed above, unless we provide you with notice of those additional purposes or gather your consent as required by law.
Personal Information Collected through the Security Camera or other Camera-Enabled Products
When you enable the recording features of your security camera or other camera-enabled products (for example, SimpliSafe’s video doorbell product), we will record, store and process video and/or audio recordings from the device, depending on how you configure the camera and its settings. This may include capturing and making available to you portions of the recording data as part of a notification or analysis of the data to identify motion or other events. We process and store Personal Information from your camera-enabled product so that we can send you alerts when there is an event. If you have the recording features enabled, during the subscription period applicable to your camera-enabled product we will capture, process and store video and audio recordings from your camera for 30 days from the date such data is first recorded ("SimpliSafe's date of first capture"). During your subscription period, you will be able to access those recordings for 30 days from SimpliSafe's date of first capture of such data. You have the option to delete and download these recordings from your account timeline during that 30-day window. If you choose to download a recording, it will not impact the retention of these videos on SimpliSafe’s systems.
NOTE: Privacy laws in your state may impose certain obligations on you and your use of the security camera(s) or other camera-enabled products. You (not SimpliSafe) are solely responsible for ensuring that you comply with any applicable laws when you use such camera-enabled products. For example, you may be required to display a notice (even inside your home) that alerts visitors to your home that you are using a security camera or other camera-enabled products that are recording audio and video. Please also consider that recording and sharing of video that involves other people may affect their privacy rights.
Cookies, Pixels, Advertising Partners and Analytics Partners
We use analytics Service Providers to collect certain Personal Information about how our Site is used. We and our advertising and analytics partners use cookies and pixels (also called web beacons) to collect certain types of Personal Information when you interact with our Site through your computer or mobile device.
A cookie is a small file containing a string of characters that is sent to your web browser when you visit a website. When you visit the website again from that web browser, the cookie allows that site to recognize your browser and, potentially, device. Cookies may store unique identifiers, user preferences and other Personal Information. You can direct your browser to clear all cookies or use the browser to understand which cookies are being set and what network requests are being made by our site. However, some website features or services may not function properly without cookies. We use cookies to improve the quality of our service, including storing user preferences, tracking user trends and providing relevant advertising to you.
Currently, we use analytics partners such as Google Analytics, Facebook, Optimizely, Amplitude and FullStory. In order to make sure you understand how our analytics partners handle your Personal Information and how they interact with our Site, you should visit the pages linked below for more information.
Google Analytics uses cookies and pixels to help us understand how visitors use our Site and to collect data on website activity. For more information regarding Google Analytics please visit
http://www.google.com/analytics/terms/us.html
. For information on how to opt out of Google Analytics, please visit
https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout/
.
Optimizely is a third-party website optimization service that analyzes your use of our Site and our relationship with you, so that we can improve our Site. For more information on the privacy practices of Optimizely, please visit
https://www.optimizely.com/privacy
. You can opt out from Optimizely at any time by following the instructions at
http://www.optimizely.com/opt_out
.
FullStory is a session recording technology that we use on our Site to detect anomalous site behavior and fix site functionality issues. For more information on the privacy practices of FullStory, please check
https://www.fullstory.com/legal/privacy-policy
.
We belong to ad networks that may use your browsing history across participating websites to show you interest-based advertisements on those websites. To learn more about interest-based advertisements and your opt-out rights and options, visit the
Digital Advertising Alliance
and the
Network Advertising Initiative
websites.
If your internet browser offers “Do Not Track” or the “Global Privacy Control” opt-out preference signal and you enable the feature, we will honor your request to opt-out of sale or sharing when you visit our Site by treating the requests as an opt-out of cookies and pixels that collect and share information for marketing purposes.
SimpliSafe Product or Account Interaction with SimpliSafe Partners
If SimpliSafe offers any product or account connections or integrations with partner products, applications, functionality or services (collectively, “Partner Products and Services”) and if you choose to enable or connect to such Partner Products and Services through the means authorized and directed by SimpliSafe and/or such partners, then you acknowledge and agree that we may share certain Personal Information about you with such partners for account authentication and management and to enable the activation, and integration with and connection to such Partner Products and Services on such partners’ platforms. For example, when you elect to use Partner Products and Services, such as SimpliSafe’s Amazon Alexa Skill, the August Smart Lock, Apple Watch or Google Assistant (as and when each is introduced), you agree that we may provide certain data about you to such partners in order to enable the activation, connection and integration with and to such Partner Products and Services you intend to use or otherwise choose to activate. In some cases, SimpliSafe or the partner will instead (or also) ask for permission to control the SimpliSafe products and services and/or Partner Products and Services that you have activated and connected to as contemplated hereunder. Your consent is required to allow any of these exchanges or requests for control and you will be able to revoke or disable it at any time.
In addition, SimpliSafe may share Personal Information with such partners with your permission. For example, when you enroll or activate Partner Products and Services, you may be asked for your permission to share certain data between SimpliSafe and our partner. SimpliSafe requires your consent before sharing Personal Information in these circumstances. We may also receive information from our partners and other sources and combine that with the Personal Information in your SimpliSafe account to determine eligibility and efficacy of our programs.
Additional information about the limited circumstances in which Personal Information from your SimpliSafe account may be shared with partners is described in the section titled "
Information We Collect and Why We Collect It
."
Any SimpliSafe data that you choose to share with a partner, either directly or by or on behalf of SimpliSafe through the authorizations, integrations and connections permitted under this Privacy Policy, is governed by that partner’s privacy policy.
Any data that SimpliSafe receives from partners will be processed and stored by SimpliSafe and will be treated in accordance with this Privacy Policy. This information may be processed in the same ways as any other data that is a part of your SimpliSafe account.
No Personal Information From Children or Teens Under Age 18
This Site is not directed to, and we do not knowingly collect any Personal Information from, children or teenagers under the age of 18. If you are under the age of 18, please do not attempt to register with us at this Site or provide any Personal Information about yourself to us. If you are under the age of 18, you may only use this Site under the supervision of your parents or guardians.
The Site does not knowingly solicit or collect personally identifiable information online from children under the age of 13 without prior verifiable parental consent. If we learn that a child under the age of 13 has submitted personally identifiable information online without parental consent, SimpliSafe will take all reasonable measures to delete such information from its databases, inform any third parties to delete such information and to not use such information for any purpose (except where necessary to protect the safety of the child or others as required or allowed by law). If you become aware of any personally identifiable information we have collected from children under 13, please use the
contact form available on our website
.
We do not have actual knowledge that we sell or share Personal Information of individuals under 16 years of age.
Third-Party Sites and Social Media
Our Site may contain links to other websites operated by third parties and may include social media features such as Facebook, Twitter and Pinterest buttons. These third-party sites may collect Personal Information about you if you click on a link, and the social media sites may automatically record Personal Information about your browsing behavior every time you visit a site that has a social media button. Your interactions with these features are governed by the privacy policy and terms of service of the company providing the link, not SimpliSafe’s Privacy Policy or Terms of Service. Accordingly, we recommend that you review the privacy policy posted on any external site before disclosing any Personal Information. Please contact those websites directly if you have any questions about their privacy policies.
Refer A Friend
If you use our “Refer A Friend” feature, we ask for your friend’s name and e-mail address. We use this Personal Information only to send the communication you requested and to monitor the effectiveness of our “Refer A Friend” feature.
Legal Proceedings
We will share Personal Information with third-party companies, organizations or individuals outside of SimpliSafe if we have a good-faith belief that access, use, preservation or disclosure of the Personal Information is reasonably necessary to:
Meet any applicable law, regulation, subpoena, legal process or governmental request.
Enforce applicable
Terms of Sale
,
Terms of Use
, and
Terms of Service
, including investigation of potential violations.
Detect, prevent or otherwise address fraud, security or technical issues.
Protect against harm to the rights, property or safety of SimpliSafe, our users, customers or the public as required or permitted by law.
Under certain circumstances, we may be required to disclose your Personal Information in response to valid requests by public authorities, including to meet national security or law enforcement requirements.
Transfer in the Event of Sale or Change of Control
If the ownership of all or substantially all of our business changes or we otherwise transfer assets relating to our business or the Site to a third party, such as by merger, acquisition, bankruptcy proceeding or otherwise, we may transfer or sell your Personal Information to the new owner. In such a case, unless permitted or otherwise directed by applicable law, your Personal Information would remain subject to the terms of the applicable privacy policy in effect at the time of such transfer.
3. ACCESS TO YOUR INFORMATION AND CHOICES
You can access and update certain Personal Information we have relating to your account by logging into your account via our online web application at
simplisafe.com
or in our mobile App. To update your contact information for your alarm monitoring and dispatch, navigate to the “Monitoring” section. To update your login information (email, password), you can navigate to the “Manage Account” section.
To update your contact information for your alarm monitoring and dispatch on our mobile App, you can log in and tap on the menu and select “Location Profile”. To update your login information on our mobile App (email, password), you can tap on the menu and select “Manage Account”.
If you have questions about the Personal Information we have about you, you can
Contact Us using this form
. You may opt out of receiving non-marketing related communications (this does not include alarm alerts and service information) from us by logging into your account and editing your notification preferences. You can opt-out of receiving marketing and promotional emails from SimpliSafe by using the opt-out or unsubscribe feature contained in the footer of our marketing emails.
You can close your online account by calling us at 800-548-9508. If you close your account, we will no longer use your online account information or share it with third parties. We may, however, retain some of your Personal Information, as allowed by law, for a period of time reasonably necessary for legitimate business purposes, archival purposes and to avoid identity theft or fraud.
4. SECURITY OF YOUR INFORMATION
We use commercially reasonable physical, technical and administrative security measures and safeguards to protect the confidentiality and security of your Personal Information. However, since the Internet is not a 100% secure environment, we cannot guarantee, ensure or warrant the security of any Personal Information you transmit to us. There is no guarantee that Personal Information may not be accessed, disclosed, altered or destroyed by breach of any of our physical, technical or managerial safeguards. Please note that e-mails and other communications you send to us through our Site are not encrypted, outside of certain channels such as secure chat, and we strongly advise you not to communicate any confidential information through these means.
5. CALIFORNIA AND OTHER STATE PRIVACY RIGHTS
If you are a resident of California, Virginia, Colorado, Connecticut,  Utah, Texas, Oregon, Montana (starting October 1, 2024), Nebraska (starting January 1, 2025), Iowa (starting January 1, 2025), Delaware (starting January 1, 2025), New Hampshire (starting January 1, 2025), or New Jersey (starting January 15, 2025) the privacy laws in those states provide you with several rights with respect to your personal information. Please see your state specific sections below for more information.
